name: DS_CPUT
description: Percentage of time over the previous minute that the system CPUs were not idle.

name: DS_CPUT_MS
description: CPU time used by MS. The value is the number of seconds of CPU time consumed by all MS threads over the sampling period divided by the number of seconds in the sampling period and multiplied by 100. The value is nominally represented as a percentage, but the value can exceed 100 when multiple threads are busy

name: DS_POWER_CONSUMPTION

name: DS_RUNQ
